data.text: The Nobel prizes are the most coveted and most potent awards of all time. Only Nobel prize winners bestows instant recognition, lifelong celebrity, and unrivaled authority around the globe. This would be best for young learners to get knowledge about the history of physics revolution through their achievements. These achievements are great indeed, and the winners join a list of some of humanity's finest representatives. Here's a sampling of notable Nobel Prize recipients of physics, and what they accomplished. (“Look up at the stars and not down at your feet. Try to make sense of what you see, and wonder about what makes the universe exist. Be curious.” – Stephen Hawking)
